author: Charmaine Ng
text:
I‚Äôve been to several gyms in Singapore, both commercial and boutique, and my experience at Anytime Fitness 537 Bedok North has truly stood out over the past year.

The staff are friendly, approachable, and always ready to help. The gym is clean, neat, and well-organized, with clear efforts to maintain a safe and comfortable environment. I appreciate how they actively remind members to wear proper footwear and re-rack weights to keep the space orderly, though of course, not everyone follows the rules all the time!

I‚Äôve also been doing Personal Training with Steve, and his professionalism and dedication are remarkable. He‚Äôs meticulous about form and consistency, always tracking my progress and the weights I lift to ensure continual improvement. Unlike some trainers who just go through the motions, Steve genuinely cares about his clients‚Äô progress and knows exactly how to help you push past your limits safely.

Overall, I highly recommend this gym,  and if you‚Äôre considering personal training, ask for Steve. You‚Äôll be in good hands!

author: Michael Thein
text: Anytime Fitness 537 Bedok North is an excellent gym ‚Äì spacious, clean, and never too crowded, so equipment is always available. The two big TV screens add a nice vibe to the training environment. Staff are super friendly and approachable, always ready to help with advice or a smile. Love the variety of free group classes like HIIT, Yoga, and Zumba. A great place to work out and feel motivated!

author: Aly
text:
I started coming here because my partner lives nearby and had been considering making this my regular gym. Everything was great during my first few visits, but yesterday was the worst experience I‚Äôve ever had in any gym and unfortunately, it‚Äôs made me reconsider coming back.

A staff member named Steve pointed out that I had placed some weight plates in the wrong spot. It was an honest mistake. I genuinely didn‚Äôt realize I had put those plates on the wrong rack. I have no problem being corrected, and I would‚Äôve gladly fixed it, but the way it was handled was disappointing. Instead of quietly letting me know, he chose to point it out in front of everyone, which was unnecessary, embarrassing and left me feeling humiliated.

I completely understand and appreciate that staff need to maintain order and uphold gym standards, but there are ways to do that with tact and professionalism. A simple, respectful reminder in private would have been much more appropriate.

As someone who struggles with anxiety, being called out publicly like that was very distressing. I always make sure to clean equipment before and after use, re-rack my weights, and often tidy up after others as well. In fact, before using the incline press machine the same day, I cleared weights left behind by the previous person without complaint, something you can easily verify on your CCTV if needed. To be treated disrespectfully despite this effort was disheartening.

Steve is a senior coach, and with that title comes the responsibility to know how to approach people respectfully. While I appreciate that he eventually apologized (after my partner spoke with him), the damage was already done. A simple ‚Äúsorry‚Äù doesn‚Äôt undo the embarrassment or the emotional impact of that moment. A public reprimand over a small, honest mistake is not the way to build a supportive community environment.

I genuinely hope this feedback leads to better communication and sensitivity toward members in the future, especially toward women who just want to feel comfortable and safe working out. For a gym that promotes community, this experience unfortunately showed the opposite.

author: Tessa Peng
text:
Steve has been training me for a few months, and I would genuinely recommend him to anyone looking for a personal trainer. He‚Äôs always professional and full of positive energy, no matter how his day has been, even when he‚Äôs not feeling his best, he still shows up with a great attitude.

What I really appreciate is how attentive he is. He pays close attention to form and corrects it right away, which has made a big difference for me. I‚Äôve also become much more confident using the equipment at the gym thanks to his guidance. Steve never forces anything I‚Äôm uncomfortable with and always tailors the workouts to fit what I need and what I can handle.

It‚Äôs honestly been such a pleasure training with him, and I always look forward to our sessions. I‚Äôm really grateful for all the support and motivation he gives!

author: lue teh
text:
I wouldn‚Äôt say this is a 5-star gym but my trainer Steve definitely a 5-stars trainer. He is paying attention to all my posture and movement while we are doing the session. He gives positive and tactical guidance to correct my posture because I have lower back issues. He even tries his best to understand my requirements as a Taekwon-Do athlete to help me to build better strength and power in performing. With his help, I got myself one gold, one silver and one bronze in my April 2025 Korea Championship.

The gym wise is not a big gym, it is small, but all the equipments are neatly arranged and in place. The gym condition is clean, aircon is cold enough (most importantly). However, it will be a plus point if the each cubicle in washroom has an alcohol sanitation dispenser to wipe the toilet seat before use, since the toilet is shared for both male and female.

author: Judy Tan
text:
I‚Äôm a new member and currently gym hopping. This is not my home gym but the moment I stepped in, there was a faint hint of essential oil. This must be the best smelling  gym in the entire world. Crowd was minimal at 10am. There is plenty of space for everyone to move around each other. Equipments are neat and clean. Will be helpful if there were more sanitation wipes. The paper towels tear easily and the sanitizer dispenser doesn‚Äôt dispense enough solution to properly clean the equipments after use. But this is no big deal because it‚Äôs so clean here already. I think I found my favourite gym
.

author: Dilly babu
text:
Outstanding Personal Trainer & Great Gym Environment!

I‚Äôve been training with Steve for a while now, and I can confidently say he is one of the best fitness trainers out there. His knowledge, dedication, and personalized approach make every session both challenging and enjoyable.

Steve takes the time to understand my fitness goals and creates a program tailored specifically to my needs. He pushes me beyond my limits while ensuring proper form and technique, which has significantly improved my strength and overall fitness. His motivation and positive attitude make even the toughest workouts feel achievable.

The gym itself is also fantastic‚Äîclean, well-equipped, and has a great atmosphere that keeps me motivated. The equipment is top-notch and the staff is friendly and supportive, creating a welcoming environment for all fitness levels.

What sets Steve apart is his genuine passion for fitness and his clients‚Äô success. He is always encouraging, supportive, and ready to adapt workouts based on progress or any physical limitations. Thanks to his guidance, I‚Äôve seen remarkable improvements in my endurance, muscle tone, and confidence.

If you‚Äôre looking for a dedicated and knowledgeable personal trainer in a great gym environment, I highly recommend Steve. He will help you achieve your fitness goals and keep you motivated every step of the way!

text:
I had always been physically weak and was very hesitant to start going to the gym. Then I met Faz, and her kind words gave me the encouragement I needed to begin this journey.

From the very start, she has been patient and supportive‚Äînever rushing me, always cheering me on as I pushed through my limitations. She understands my hesitations and has been dedicated to guiding me at every step of progress.

Six months on, I can see real changes‚Äînot only in my body, but also in my mindset. I feel stronger, both physically and mentally. I‚Äôve committed to another six months with Faz, knowing she will continue to help me become stronger and better.

Thank you, Faz, for your unwavering support. If you‚Äôre looking for a professional, patient, and results-driven trainer, I highly recommend Faz.
